data: # Proposal: To sort a content list for Bodhi against the timeline and the share-pool value
creator: 0xafeeeaa59c0d099ab957a428fa55f546d28fbdb0

data: But now, there is only one list, which is sorted by the share-pool value. The order in the list is stable. This is not good for people who invest in the content, as well as the income of creators. Investor needs speculation opportunities, and creators need content share trades, which will give creators transaction fees.
creator: 0xafeeeaa59c0d099ab957a428fa55f546d28fbdb0

data: If we create lists sorted by the share-pool value changes in a day, a week, and a month. the position of content in the timeline lists will be dynamic. In order to capture the attention of the audience, people will invest in content in a short time and will withdraw the share investment after the curation. This will lead to the price of content share fluctuation. Assets price fluctuation will bring speculation.  And authors will get money from speculation.
creator: 0xafeeeaa59c0d099ab957a428fa55f546d28fbdb0

data: Bodhi now is permissionless accessible, the only way to distract the content value is to capture the audience's attention. most of the audience may be attracted by the filtered list or by the author. In the web2 social media platform, the most common operation for us is to follow some author, or some list, rather than content itself. So to sort the most valuable contents as a list is an excellent product design.
creator: 0xafeeeaa59c0d099ab957a428fa55f546d28fbdb0

data: After days of launch, the enthusiasm of Bodhi is fading away. As I conclude from my traditional media experience, only attention, traffic, or knowledge are the most significant for the content value. If the content is designed to be permissionless accessible, only attention and traffic can be value-captured by the content assets.
